sentences.english: Look for the green seal that says USDA Organic.
sentences.chinese: 尋找標有“美國農業部有機”的綠色圖章。

sentences.english: Learn how to make some all-occasion cards using rubber stamps with flower designs.
sentences.chinese: 瞭解如何使一些全場合用花卡設計橡皮圖章。

sentences.english: Then the lovely young mother showed the signet ring as proof.
sentences.chinese: 這位年輕又迷人的母親當衆出示了圖章戒指以作證明。

sentences.english: RUBBER STAMP SIGNATURES OF THE BENEFICIARY ON DOCUMENTS ARE NOT ACCEPTABLE。
sentences.chinese: 蓋有受益人橡皮圖章的單據將不予接受。

sentences.english: There is no stamp on the stamp.
sentences.chinese: 那張郵票上沒有蓋圖章。

sentences.english: So we have to pluck the medallions from the crown.
sentences.chinese: 所以我們要拿出王冠裏的圖章。

sentences.english: Seal Engraving To the Chinese, a seal was for many centuries a symbol of power.
sentences.chinese: 篆刻千百年來，對中國人來說，圖章是權利的象徵。

sentences.english: Notice how the image of the serpent is significant even in the sigil at the bottom of the page.
sentences.chinese: 公告的蛇是怎樣的形象，甚至在很大的圖章在谷底頁。

sentences.english: She got that pair of Tianhuang seal again and noticed that its brocade box had been renewed.
sentences.chinese: 她又找出那一對田黃圖章，發現已換了簇新的錦盒。

sentences.english: You must rubber-stamp those letters before you post them.
sentences.chinese: 在郵寄那些封信以前，你必須在上面蓋上橡皮圖章。

sentences.english: In practice, they act as expensive rubber stamps.
sentences.chinese: 而在實際上，他們只是價錢昂貴的橡皮圖章而已。

sentences.english: I born and live in Beijing. I am a staff in an AD. company.
sentences.chinese: 我是途勝圖章的北京人，現在是一家廣告公司的職員。
